ENTRY       EC 5.4.99.58                Enzyme
NAME        methylornithine synthase;
            PylB
CLASS       Isomerases;
            Intramolecular transferases;
            Transferring other groups
SYSNAME     L-lysine carboxy-aminomethylmutase
REACTION    L-lysine = (3R)-3-methyl-D-ornithine [RN:R10010]
ALL_REAC    R10010
SUBSTRATE   L-lysine [CPD:C00047]
PRODUCT     (3R)-3-methyl-D-ornithine [CPD:C20277]
COMMENT     The enzyme is a member of the superfamily of S-adenosyl-L-methionine-dependent radical (radical AdoMet) enzymes. Binds a [4Fe-4S] cluster that is coordinated by 3 cysteines and an exchangeable S-adenosyl-L-methionine molecule. The reaction is part of the biosynthesis pathway of pyrrolysine, a naturally occurring amino acid found in some archaeal methyltransferases.
